<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Teen Killed,0130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teen-Ager Killed After Plunging 130 Feet</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 17-year-old died after plunging at
least 130 feet from the top of the New Haven Veterans Memorial
Coliseum, where he had planned to attend a rock concert, authorities
said.
   Steven Frank Piech of Danbury was on the top level of the parking
garage above the coliseum when he slipped, held on for a moment and
then fell to the sidewalk, witnesses told police.
   One witness, Tom Corso, flagged down a police officer, and
another witness called for medical help on his truck radio,
authorities said Sunday.
   ``We couldn't believe what happened,'' Corso said.
   Piech had arrived early for Saturday night's concert by Ozzy
Osbourne and Anthrax when he fell, authorities said.
</TEXT>
