<2ND_LINE>PM-Lebanon-Violence, 4th Ld-Writethru, a0535,0282</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Car Bombs Explode In Lebanon</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 4 grafs to update with three wounded in village.
Picks up 4th graf pvs ``The hospital...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Car bombs exploded today near Syrian army
checkpoints in the capital and the Bekaa Valley, killing one person
and injuring at least nine, police said.
   Six civilians were injured and one was killed when a car packed
with about 110 pounds of TNT exploded at 2:20 p.m. in front of
Baydoun Hospital in Moslem west Beirut, police said.
   Three people were injured at 1:30 p.m., police said, when a car
exploded near a Syrian army checkpoint in the village of Saadnayel,
24 miles east of Beirut.
   The police spokesman said the car that blew up in the village
also contained about 110 pounds of TNT.
   The hospital took the brunt of the explosion in Beirut. A nurse,
who refused to give her name, said the force of the blast hurled
most of the 36 patients out of their beds as shrapnel tore through
the windows.
   ``Luckily there were no operations under way,'' she said. ``The
explosion would have definitely shaken the hands of the surgeons,
which could have affected the lives of the patients.''
   None of the Syrian troops manning a checkpoint about 75 yards
from the hospital was injured, police said. The soldiers cordoned
off the area after the explosion as the wounded were taken to the
American University Hospital about six blocks away.
   The explosions were the 19th and 20th car bombings in Lebanon
this year. Police have said 115 people were killed and 279 wounded
in the previous car bombings.
</TEXT>
