<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Colombia     12-05 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Colombia,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspected Death Squad Kills 6</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen opened fire on the patrons of a
bar in a northwestern town and killed six people, police said Monday.
   The attack Sunday in the town of Puerto Valdivia, 195 miles
northwest of Bogota, appeared to be the work of a right-wing death
squad, they said.
   The victims included a member of a Marxist group, the Patriotic
Union, and a guerrilla of the Colombian Revolutionary Armed Forces,
police said.
   Death squads have killed more than 900 people in Colombia in the
past four years.
   This year, the squads have killed 282 people in 21 massacres.
Most of the victims were members of the Patriotic Union.
