<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--BaptistryDoor     12-05 0139</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Baptistry Door,0142</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`Door of Paradise' To Be Replaced With Replica</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FLORENCE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ``Door of Paradise,'' a 15th century
portal that graces the St. John baptistry, will be removed for
restoration and replaced by a replica, officials said Monday.
   The 16-foot-by-8-foot bronze door, damaged by time and pollution,
is to be removed at the beginning of 1989 and replaced by a replica
in 1990. Until then, wood will fill the opening in the octagonal St.
John baptistry.
   The original door, expected to be restored by 1995, is to be kept
in the museum of the nearby Duomo cathedral to protect it from
further damage.
   The door's 10 panels, which depict scenes from the Bible, were
sculpted by Lorenzo Ghiberti between 1425 and 1452.
   Michelangelo was said to have called the work the ``Door of
Paradise.''
</TEXT>
