<2ND_LINE>AM-Weatherpage Weather,0332</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Placid Weather Across Most Of Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Fair, mild weather continued Monday across much of the nation,
with freezing afternoon temperatures largely confined to the
northern Atlantic Coast region and the Rockies.
   Snow showers spread over northern Maine. During the previous
night, light snow fell across much of Vermont, with 4 inches
reported at Dorset and 3 inches at Ball Mountain.
   Temperatures in Vermont dipped close to zero during the night,
with a morning low of one degree above zero at Canaan.
   A low pressure system brought showers to the northern Pacific
Coast.
   Clouds and fog spread over much of the West during the morning,
with dense fog reported in California's central valleys.
   Temperatures were generally above 50 by early afternoon from the
high Plains through the lower half of the Mississippi Valley to the
southern Atlantic Coast, with readings in the 60s over southern
Texas and the Southeast, and in the 70s in southern and central
Florida, Texas' lower Rio Grande Valley and extreme southern
California and southern Arizona.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 p.m. EST ranged from 13
degrees at Limestone, Maine, to 81 at Thermal, Calif. Monday
morning's official low was 12 degrees below zero at Jackson, Wyo.
   For Tuesday, scattered showers were forecast across Washington
and Oregon, with rain likely in western Washington. Scattered snow
showers were forecast over northern Maine.
   Highs in the 20s were predicted across northern Maine; in the 30s
from Minnesota to eastern Montana, and across upstate New York and
northern New England; into the 40s from the northern Pacific Coast
inland, and through the Dakotas to the northern Atlantic Coast;
above 60 from the southern and central coast of California through
southern New Mexico and through the lower half of the Mississippi
Valley to the southern Atlantic Coast; and in the 70s over southern
and central Florida, southern Louisiana, southern and central Texas,
southern Arizona and southern California.
</TEXT>
