<HEAD>Fiat USA Names Chairman, New President</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Only version planned.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fiat USA Inc. said Monday that Furio M. Colombo
has been appointed chairman of the U.S. subsidiary of Italy's
largest private company and Vittorio C. Vellano has been named its
president.
   Colombo, whose title is new, has been president of Fiat USA since
1983 and before that was an executive with Olivetti Co. and the
Italian Radio and Television System, Fiat said in a news release
issued from its New York City headquarters.
   Vellano has been vice president of Fiat USA since 1987.
   Fiat USA oversees North American activities of the Fiat Group,
and handles products including Alfa Romeo and Ferrari automobiles,
Iveco trucks and industrial and agricultural machinery, fibers,
chemicals and biological engineering businesses.
